{{/*
Render a simple scalar value with optional label and unit.
Fields:

* `label` (string, optional): A label to display before the value.
* `value` (scalar): The value to display.
* `unit` (string, optional): A unit to display after the value.

Opening tag comes right after this comment's closing tag
because this helper gets used in a lot of contexts
where an extra space looks ugly.
That's also why there's no trailing newline in this file.
*/}}<span class="scalar">
    {{- if (index . "label") -}}
        <span class="scalar-label">{{ .label }}</span>
    {{- end }}
    <span class="scalar-value">{{ .value }}</span>
    {{- if (index . "unit") -}}
        <span class="scalar-unit">{{ .unit }}</span>
    {{- end -}}
</span>